children.subject: I got a response from Denero and he said that since the course is full of grad students, no undergrads can enroll.
Is there a chance the course will expand?
will the lectures be webcasted in case we just want to listen?

history.content:
Prof DeNero asked me to post this information regarding enrollment into CS288:

CS 288 will only enroll EECS/CS graduate students until at least mid-December in order to determine the amount of demand for the course from graduate students. At that time, if it appears that there is some room for undergraduates, we'll announce an enrollment policy. Until then, we don't have any information about prerequisites, enrollment procedures, or capacity. Based on limited data so far, we believe there is a good chance that the course will fill with graduate students.
